      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Acetanilide is less reactive than aniline toward electrophilic substitution. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbElWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7c7d49c3891c4d2ec44b347628c77f687e631904/OChem_16_04_013.jpg\" alt=\"Acetanilide has benzene ring bonded to an N H group. The nitrogen atom is bonded to the carbonyl group which, in turn, is bonded to a methyl group.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "The nitrogen electrons are donated to the nearby carbonyl group by resonance and are less available to the ring."
